EVENT_DESCRIPTION: “What happened was a waterspout. It rained 150 millimeters [or 150 liters per square meter] for about half an hour and, in the lower area of ​​Brinches, there were floods”, explained the president of the Municipality of Serpa, João Efigénio Palma, to the Lusa agency.  According to the mayor, “no one was expecting” this “meteorological phenomenon located in Brinches”, because what was predicted “was thunderstorms and rain, but nothing with this volume”.  Contacted today by Lusa, the Baixo Alentejo Sub-Regional Emergency and Civil Protection Command indicated that, “from 6 pm” on Friday, it received the first warnings of flooding in Brinches, in houses and public roads.
